Instructions for a 64 bit computer.

1. Run:
	git clone https://github.com/ccny-ros-pkg/ccny_camera_drivers.git

2. Add the package to rosws(rosws set):
	rosws set ccny_camera_drivers/

3. Download the 64 bit mvVirtualDevice drivers for the bluefox camera
	http://www.matrix-vision.com/mvvirtualdevice-442.html
	(current one is mvVirtualDevicex86_64_ABI2-2.4.2.tgz

4. Place the tgz in ccny_mvVirtualDevice/build/
	(make the build folder if it does not exist)

5. Get the Makefile out of documentation/install_bluefox/
	and place into: fuerte_workspace/ccny_mvVirtualDevice/

6. Go to the /ccny_mvVirtualDevice/build/ directory and run:
	md5sum mvVirtualDevice-x86_64_ABI2-2.4.2.tgz > ../mvVirtualDevice-x86_64_ABI2-2.4.2.tgz.md5sum

7. rosmake ccny_mvVirtualDevice

8. rosmake mv_bluefox_driver

